  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to strengthen capacities to undertake reforms to advance peacebuilding and transitional justice processes in Sri Lanka</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM in Sri Lanka will provide technical, capacity development, financial, coordination, monitoring and knowledge management support across the four outcomes of the Peacebuilding Priority Plan (PPP), whilst also ensuring that the guiding principles as outlined in the PPP are adhered to. This will include promoting a reconciliation and transitional justice process that is principled, victim-centric, rights-based, nationally owned, and sensitive to the specific concerns of women and youth.</narrative>
  </description>
